## Migration

Inline export of test-run__hello-world__1:
```sh
bun -e '
import { Database } from "bun:sqlite";
const db = new Database(".abt/abt.db", { readonly: true });
const flow = db.query("SELECT * FROM flows WHERE id = ?").get("test-run__hello-world__1");
const localRows = db.query("SELECT path, value FROM flow_local WHERE flow_id = ?").all("test-run__hello-world__1");
const globalRows = db.query("SELECT path, value FROM flow_global WHERE flow_id = ?").all("test-run__hello-world__1");
const local = {};
for (const r of localRows) {
  // un-flatten path "a.b.c" → nested object
  const segs = r.path.split(".");
  let cur = local;
  for (let i = 0; i < segs.length - 1; i++) cur = cur[segs[i]] ??= {};
  cur[segs[segs.length-1]] = JSON.parse(r.value);
}
const global = {};
for (const r of globalRows) {
  const segs = r.path.split(".");
  let cur = global;
  for (let i = 0; i < segs.length - 1; i++) cur = cur[segs[i]] ??= {};
  cur[segs[segs.length-1]] = JSON.parse(r.value);
}
const doc = { ...flow, local, global };
await Bun.write(".abt/flows/test-run__hello-world__1.json", JSON.stringify(doc, null, 2));
'
```

Run once before the DB is removed. Verify with `cat`. Then `git rm .abt/abt.db`.

## Order of operations

1. Rename db.ts → paths.ts (so subsequent edits compile against paths.ts).
2. Replace repos.ts.
3. Update commands.ts call sites.
4. Update tree.ts call sites.
5. Update mermaid.ts call sites.
6. Update index.ts.
7. Run `bunx tsc --noEmit` → fix any drift.
8. Run migration script → produce JSON file.
9. Run hello-world end-to-end against new store with the dev `bun index.ts` (the `./abt` binary stays as my driver).
10. Remove .abt/abt.db, update .gitignore.
11. Run `bun test`.
12. Commit.

## Risk assessment

Low. Drop-in API replacement. Single integration test exercises the full loop. Migration touches one row.

## Complexity

0.5. Mechanical refactor with explicit mapping. No design decisions left, no external dependencies, no concurrency. Slightly above 0 because path-resolution semantics shift from flat keys to nested objects and the migration must un-flatten — non-trivial but covered by the integration test.

## Frontend / Backend

Backend only. No UI. No HTTP. Just file I/O and process flow.
